Description: Calculates N, P2O5 and K2O fertilization requirements following
    the Disciplinari di Produzione Integrata (DPI) Emilia-Romagna – method of
    the balance (Allegato 2) and the "Scheda a dose Standard" simplified
    method. It implements the nutrient balance model used by FertDPI /
    Fert_Office (v1.26, Febbraio 2026) and accounts for crop demand (A), soil
    supply (B1/B2/A-Mantenimento), leaching (C1, C2, H), immobilization (D),
    previous crop residues (E), organic fertilization (F, F_org), and natural
    deposition (G). Includes soil texture classification (USDA and DPI
    groupings), maximum allowed doses (MAS), Olsen P and exchangeable K
    availability classes, soil pH / carbonate / CEC classification,
    fertilization distribution plan with organic and mineral fertilisers,
    end-of-cycle soil P and K estimation, NDVI-based variable rate estimation
    (calibration and Holland & Schepers), and tools for integrated and
    precision nutrient management.
